President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These appointments include Gina S. Farrisee as Assistant Secretary for Human Resources and Administration at the Department of Veterans Affairs, Megan H. Mack as Officer for Civil Rights and Civil Liberties at the Department of Homeland Security, and Melissa Savage and C. Kenneth Smith as members of the Board of Directors of the Valles Caldera Trust. Other appointments include David Sanders as Chairperson of the Commission to Eliminate Child Abuse and Neglect Fatalities, Theresa Martha Covington, Patricia M. Martin, Michael R. Petit, Jennifer Rodriguez, and David Rubin as members of the same commission, Rosemary A. Joyce as a member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee, and Alice T. Germond and Azita Raji as members of the President's Commission on White House Fellowships. President Obama expressed his honor in having these talented individuals join his administration and serve the country.